here was a stirring and a ⟦fluttering⟧ all through the farm buildings. Word had gone round during the day that old Major, the prize Middle White boar, had had a strange dream on the previous night and wished to communicate it to the other animals.", "marked": true, "note": "새가 날개를 빠르게 떨거나, 깃발이 가볍게 펄럭이는 모습. stirring(포유류·전체)과 짝지어 fluttering(조류 특유)로 농장의 모든 종류의 동물이 깨어남을 함축.", "sid": "c1s003"}, {"word": "farm buildings", "pos": "n.phr.", "pron": "/fɑːm ˈbɪldɪŋz/", "mean": "농장 건물들 (외양간·헛간·축사 등 부속 건물 전체)", "ctx": "As soon as the light in the bedroom went out there was a stirring and a fluttering all through the ⟦farm buildings⟧. Word had gone round during the day that old Major, the prize Middle White boar, had had a strange dream on the previous night and wished to communicate it to the other animals.", "marked": true, "note": "주거용 집(farmhouse)과 구분되는 생산·축산 공간. Mr. Jones의 침실(권력의 중심)과 대조되는 피지배자의 영역.", "sid": "c1s003"}, {"word": "word had gone round", "pos": "idiom", "pron": "/wɜːd həd ɡɒn raʊnd/", "mean": "소문이 돌았다. 소식이 퍼졌다", "ctx": "As soon as the light in the bedroom went out there was a stirring and a fluttering all through the farm buildings. ⟦Word had gone round⟧ during the day that old Major, the prize Middle White boar, had had a strange dream on the previous night and wished to communicate it to the other animals.", "marked": true, "note": "", "sid": "c1s003"}, {"word": "prize", "pos": "adj.", "pron": "/praɪz/", "mean": "수상 경력이 있는, 우수한 (가축 품평회에서 입상한)", "ctx": "As soon as the light in the bedroom went out there was a stirring and a fluttering all through the farm buildings. Word had gone round during the day that old Major, the ⟦prize⟧ Middle White boar, had had a strange dream on the previous night and wished to communicate it to the other animals.", "marked": true, "note": "축산 어휘. 가축 품평회(agricultural show)에서 상을 받은 혈통 좋은 개체. Old Major가 Willingdon Beauty라는 전시명으로 상을 받은 적이 있음(c1s004에서 부연).", "sid": "c1s003"}, {"word": "Middle White", "pos": "n.", "pron": "/ˈmɪdl waɪt/", "mean": "미들 화이트 (영국 돼지 품종)", "ctx": "As soon as the light in the bedroom went out there was a stirring and a fluttering all through the farm buildings. Word had gone round during the day that old Major, the prize ⟦Middle White⟧ boar, had had a strange dream on the previous night and wished to communicate it to the other animals.", "marked": true, "note": "19세기 후반 영국 요크셔에서 확립된 영국 토종 돼지 품종. 풍부한 육질로 유명하며 19~20세기 초 영국에서 가장 사랑받은 식용 돼지. Old Major가 영국에서 가장 영국적인 돼지임을 강조, 알레고리의 영국 토착성을 시각화.", "sid": "c1s003"}, {"word": "boar", "pos": "n.", "pron": "/bɔːr/", "mean": "수퇘지 (특히 거세하지 않은 종돈)", "ctx": "As soon as the light in the bedroom went out there was a stirring and a fluttering all through the farm buildings. Word had gone round during the day that old Major, the prize Middle White ⟦boar⟧, had had a strange dream on the previous night and wished to communicate it to the other animals.", "marked": true, "note": "", "sid": "c1s003"}, {"word": "strange dream", "pos": "n.phr.", "pron": "/streɪndʒ driːm/", "mean": "이상한 꿈, 기묘한 꿈", "ctx": "As soon as the light in the bedroom went out there was a stirring and a fluttering all through the farm buildings. Word had gone round during the day that old Major, the prize Middle White boar, had had a ⟦strange dream⟧ on the previous night and wished to communicate it to the other animals.", "marked": true, "note": "strange는 단순히 \"이상한\"이 아니라 비일상적이고 예언적인 뉘앙스. 성서·신화에서 영웅·예언자가 꿈을 통해 계시를 받는 전통(요셉·다니엘·구약 선지자)을 환기.", "sid": "c1s003"}, {"word": "communicate", "pos": "v.", "pron": "/kəˈmjuːnɪkeɪt/", "mean": "전달하다. 알리다", "ctx": "As soon as the light in the bedroom went out there was a stirring and a fluttering all through the farm buildings. Word had gone round during the day that old Major, the prize Middle White boar, had had a strange dream on the previous night and wished to ⟦communicate⟧ it to the other animals.", "marked": true, "note": "Orwell이 tell이 아닌 communicate를 선택한 것은 Old Major의 메시지가 공식적·정치적 선언임을 격상시킨다. 농장 동물이 단순히 이야기를 듣는 것이 아니라 교의(doctrine)를 전수받는 장면.", "sid": "c1s003"}, {"word": "barn", "pos": "n.", "pron": "/bɑːrn/", "mean": "헛간 (곡식·건초·가축을 보관하는 큰 농장 건물)", "ctx": "Word had gone round during the day that old Major, the prize Middle White boar, had had a strange dream on the previous night and wished to communicate it to the other animals. It had been agreed that they should all meet in the big ⟦barn⟧ as soon as Mr. Jones was safely out of the way.", "marked": true, "note": "농장의 가장 큰 공동 공간. 가축이 모일 수 있는 유일한 집회 장소, 동물들이 다 같이 만나기에 자연스러운 장소이자, 공적 사건이 일어날 무대로 미리 설정된다.", "sid": "c1s003"}, {"word": "safely", "pos": "adv.", "pron": "/ˈseɪfli/", "mean": "안전하게, 확실하게 (위험·방해 없이)", "ctx": "Word had gone round during the day that old Major, the prize Middle White boar, had had a strange dream on the previous night and wished to communicate it to the other animals. It had been agreed that they should all meet in the big barn as soon as Mr. Jones was ⟦safely⟧ out of the way.", "marked": true, "note": "여기서 safely out of the way는 \"안전하게 방해되지 않게\", 동물들의 입장에서 Mr. Jones가 확실히 사라진 상태를 의미. 평소 안전을 위협하던 존재가 지금은 위협 요소로 뒤집힌 시점의 어휘 선택.", "sid": "c1s003"}, {"word": "out of the way", "pos": "idiom", "pron": "/aʊt əv ðə weɪ/", "mean": "(방해되지 않게) 물러나, 사라져, 자리를 비켜", "ctx": "Word had gone round during the day that old Major, the prize Middle White boar, had had a strange dream on the previous night and wished to communicate it to the other animals. It had been agreed that they should all meet in the big barn as soon as Mr. Jones was safely ⟦out of the way⟧.", "marked": true, "note": "물리적으로 길에서 비켜난 상태 또는 비유적으로 방해되지 않는 상태. 누군가를 제거·치워야 할 대상으로 객체화하는 어법.", "sid": "c1s003"}, {"word": "exhibit", "pos": "v.", "pron": "/ɪɡˈzɪbɪt/", "mean": "전시하다, (품평회·박람회에서) 출품하다", "ctx": "Old Major (so he was always called, though the name under which he had been ⟦exhibited⟧ was Willingdon Beauty) was so highly regarded on the farm that everyone was quite ready to lose an hour’s sleep in order to hear what he had to say.", "marked": true, "note": "", "sid": "c1s004"}, {"word": "Willingdon Beauty", "pos": "n.pr.", "pron": "/ˈwɪlɪŋdən ˈbjuːti/", "mean": "윌링던 뷰티 (Old Major의 전시명)", "ctx": "Old Major (so he was always called, though the name under which he had been exhibited was ⟦Willingdon Beauty⟧) was so highly regarded on the farm that everyone was quite ready to lose an hour’s sleep in order to hear what he had to say.", "marked": true, "note": "Willingdon은 농장이 위치한 지명. Beauty는 가축 품평회에서 잘생긴·우수한 개체에 흔히 붙는 수식명. 인간이 상품적 외양에 맞춰 부여한 이름.", "sid": "c1s004"}, {"word": "regarded", "pos": "v.pp. (as adj.)", "pron": "/rɪˈɡɑːrdɪd/", "mean": "여겨지는, 평가받는 (highly/well/poorly + regarded 형태로 자주 쓰임)", "ctx": "Old Major (so he was always called, though the name under which he had been exhibited was Willingdon Beauty) was so highly ⟦regarded⟧ on the farm that everyone was quite ready to lose an hour’s sleep in order to hear what he had to say.", "marked": true, "note": "수동태 형용사, Major가 농장 동물들에 의해 그렇게 여겨진다. Major의 권위가 내재적이 아니라 공동체의 인정에서 비롯됨을 어휘가 명시.", "sid": "c1s004"}, {"word": "lose an hour’s sleep", "pos": "idiom", "pron": "/luːz ən aʊərz sliːp/", "mean": "한 시간의 잠을 희생하다", "ctx": "Old Major (so he was always called, though the name under which he had been exhibited was Willingdon Beauty) was so highly regarded on the farm that everyone was quite ready to ⟦lose an hour’s sleep⟧ in order to hear what he had to say.", "marked": true, "note": "잠은 농장 동물의 가장 기본적·소중한 휴식. 그것을 기꺼이 포기할 만큼 Old Major의 말이 가치 있다는 대가의 척도. 영어에서 lose sleep over X는 X 때문에 잠 못 이루다의 관용 표현, Orwell은 이 익숙한 어법을 살짝 비틀어 자발적 희생의 뉘앙스로 사용.", "sid": "c1s004"}, {"word": "in order to", "pos": "conj.phr.", "pron": "/ɪn ˈɔːrdər tuː/", "mean": "~하기 위하여 (목적의 격식 표현)", "ctx": "Old Major (so he was always called, though the name under which he had been exhibited was Willingdon Beauty) was so highly regarded on the farm that everyone was quite ready to lose an hour’s sleep ⟦in order to⟧ hear what he had to say.", "marked": true, "note": "", "sid": "c1s004"}, {"word": "raised platform", "pos": "n.phr.", "pron": "/reɪzd ˈplætfɔːrm/", "mean": "높이 올린 단·연단", "ctx": "At one end of the big barn, on a sort of ⟦raised platform⟧, Major was already ensconced on his bed of straw, under a lantern which hung from a beam.", "marked": true, "note": "a sort of(일종의, 약화 표현)가 붙어 정식 연단이 아닌 임시·즉석으로 만든 높은 자리임을 함축. 그러나 높이라는 위계의 시각적 표지는 그대로 작동.", "sid": "c1s005"}, {"word": "ensconced", "pos": "v.pp.", "pron": "/ɪnˈskɒnst/", "mean": "자리 잡고 안락하게 앉아 있는, (자리에) 단단히 자리 잡은", "ctx": "At one end of the big barn, on a sort of raised platform, Major was already ⟦ensconced⟧ on his bed of straw, under a lantern which hung from a beam.", "marked": true, "note": "왕이나 권위자가 옥좌에 앉아 있는 듯한 어조. Orwell이 돼지가 짚더미 위에 누워 있다는 평범한 상황에 굳이 이 격식 어휘를 쓴 것은 의도적 부조화·격상(elevation), 시각적 비루함과 어휘적 위엄의 충돌이 미묘한 아이러니를 낳음.", "sid": "c1s005"}, {"word": "bed of straw", "pos": "n.phr.", "pron": "/bɛd əv strɔː/", "mean": "짚더미로 만든 잠자리", "ctx": "At one end of the big barn, on a sort of raised platform, Major was already ensconced on his ⟦bed of straw⟧, under a lantern which hung from a beam.", "marked": true, "note": "가축에게 깔아주는 가장 기본적이고 비루한 잠자리. ensconced on his bed of straw는 격식 동사(ensconced)와 비격식 명사(bed of straw)가 충돌하는 어법, 옥좌에 앉은 느낌과 짚더미에 누운 현실이 한 구절 안에서 부딪힌다.", "sid": "c1s005"}, {"word": "beam", "pos": "n.", "pron": "/biːm/", "mean": "들보, 대들보 (건물의 천장을 가로지르는 굵은 목재)", "ctx": "At one end of the big barn, on a sort of raised platform, Major was already ensconced on his bed of straw, under a lantern which hung from a ⟦beam⟧.", "marked": true, "note": "전통적 영국 헛간의 노출된 오크 들보. a lantern which hung from a beam은 빛이 위에서 내려오는 구도, 무대 조명처럼 Old Major를 비추는 광원.", "sid": "c1s005"}, {"word": "stout", "pos": "adj.", "pron": "/staʊt/", "mean": "(몸집이) 통통한, 다부진", "ctx": "He was twelve years old and had lately grown rather ⟦stout⟧, but he was still a majestic-looking pig, with a wise and benevolent appearance in spite of the fact that his tushes had never been cut.", "marked": true, "note": "Orwell이 fat이 아니라 stout를 쓴 것은 의도적, Old Major의 통통함을 비루함이 아니라 원숙함·연륜