te": "물리적으로 자리에 앉다의 의미와 동시에, 정치적 함의, 돼지들이 immediately in front of the platform에 자리잡는 것은 권력 중심부 점유의 첫 신호다.", "sid": "c1s006"}, {"word": "perch", "pos": "v.", "pron": "/pɜːtʃ/", "mean": "(새가) 앉다. 횃대에 앉다", "ctx": "The hens ⟦perched⟧ themselves on the window-sills, the pigeons fluttered up to the rafters, the sheep and cows lay down behind the pigs and began to chew the cud.", "marked": true, "note": "새가 높은 곳에 앉는 동작에 특화된 동사. 일반적 'sit'과 달리 불안정한 균형과 높이의 뉘앙스가 포함된다.", "sid": "c1s006"}, {"word": "window-sill", "pos": "n.", "pron": "/ˈwɪndəʊsɪl/", "mean": "창턱", "ctx": "The hens perched themselves on the ⟦window-sills⟧, the pigeons fluttered up to the rafters, the sheep and cows lay down behind the pigs and began to chew the cud.", "marked": true, "note": "창문 안쪽의 평평한 턱. 닭들이 바닥이 아닌 창턱에 앉는다는 것은 그들의 주변부적 위치를 공간적으로 표현한다.", "sid": "c1s006"}, {"word": "flutter", "pos": "v.", "pron": "/ˈflʌtə(r)/", "mean": "푸드덕거리며 날다. 펄럭이다", "ctx": "The hens perched themselves on the window-sills, the pigeons ⟦fluttered⟧ up to the rafters, the sheep and cows lay down behind the pigs and began to chew the cud.", "marked": true, "note": "", "sid": "c1s006"}, {"word": "rafter", "pos": "n.", "pron": "/ˈrɑːftə(r)/", "mean": "서까래", "ctx": "The hens perched themselves on the window-sills, the pigeons fluttered up to the ⟦rafters⟧, the sheep and cows lay down behind the pigs and began to chew the cud.", "marked": true, "note": "지붕을 지지하는 경사진 나무 보. 헛간 가장 높은 곳. 비둘기가 여기 앉음으로써 헛간 내 수직 위계의 정점에 위치한다. 그러나 이는 주변적 정점이지 권력의 정점은 아니다.", "sid": "c1s006"}, {"word": "chew the cud", "pos": "idiom", "pron": "/tʃuː ðə kʌd/", "mean": "되새김질하다", "ctx": "The hens perched themselves on the window-sills, the pigeons fluttered up to the rafters, the sheep and cows lay down behind the pigs and began to ⟦chew the cud⟧.", "marked": true, "note": "반추동물이 한 번 삼킨 풀을 다시 끌어올려 씹는 행위. 비유적으로는 깊이 숙고하다의 의미도 있지만, 여기서는 정반대로, 양과 소의 기계적·수동적·비사고적 행동을 환기시킨다. 이들의 비판적 사고 부재가 작품 전반에 걸쳐 활용될 것이다.", "sid": "c1s006"}, {"word": "stripe", "pos": "n.", "pron": "/straɪp/", "mean": "줄무늬", "ctx": "A white ⟦stripe⟧ down his nose gave him a somewhat stupid appearance, and in fact he was not of first-rate intelligence, but he was universally respected for his steadiness of character and tremendous powers of work.", "marked": true, "note": "", "sid": "c1s007"}, {"word": "cart-horse", "pos": "n.", "pron": "/ˈkɑːt hɔːs/", "mean": "짐마차 끄는 말, 역마", "ctx": "The two ⟦cart-horses⟧, Boxer and Clover, came in together, walking very slowly and setting down their vast hairy hoofs with great care lest there should be some small animal concealed in the straw.", "marked": true, "note": "경마용 race-horse의 대척점. 무거운 짐을 끄는 노동용 말로, 보통 Shire나 Clydesdale 같은 대형 품종이다. 단어 자체가 노동 계급성을 함의한다.", "sid": "c1s007"}, {"word": "hoof", "pos": "n. (pl. hoofs/hooves)", "pron": "/huːf/", "mean": "(말·소 등의) 발굽", "ctx": "The two cart-horses, Boxer and Clover, came in together, walking very slowly and setting down their vast hairy ⟦hoofs⟧ with great care lest there should be some small animal concealed in the straw.", "marked": true, "note": "Orwell은 고전적 복수형 hoofs를 쓴다 (현대는 hooves가 더 일반적). vast hairy hoofs의 두운 h-h가 육중함의 음성적 효과를 만든다.", "sid": "c1s007"}, {"word": "lest", "pos": "conj.", "pron": "/lest/", "mean": "~하지 않도록, ~할까 봐", "ctx": "The two cart-horses, Boxer and Clover, came in together, walking very slowly and setting down their vast hairy hoofs with great care ⟦lest⟧ there should be some small animal concealed in the straw.", "marked": true, "note": "", "sid": "c1s007"}, {"word": "conceal", "pos": "v.", "pron": "/kənˈsiːl/", "mean": "감추다. 숨기다", "ctx": "The two cart-horses, Boxer and Clover, came in together, walking very slowly and setting down their vast hairy hoofs with great care lest there should be some small animal ⟦concealed⟧ in the straw.", "marked": true, "note": "", "sid": "c1s007"}, {"word": "mare", "pos": "n.", "pron": "/meə(r)/", "mean": "암말", "ctx": "Clover was a stout motherly ⟦mare⟧ approaching middle life, who had never quite got her figure back after 